      "acceptanceCriteria": "QOI (NIH) must be directly the regulatory acceptance metric with no surrogate mapping; QOI relevance demonstrated across full COU operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the direct regulatory metric; however, the model predicts volume-averaged NIH while the clinical concern is peak local hemolysis in gap regions. A surrogate mapping is implicitly applied. Achieved level 3 against required level 5."
    },
